definition.value: A direct appraisal of a patient's condition by a physical medicine and rehabilition specialist that is based on a physical exam, medical history, and the patient's account of symptoms.

value.value: A test that involves the administration of intravenous contrast and X-ray imaging of the urinary tract. The iodinated contrast flows through the renal vasculature and filtered into the collecting system highlighting the anatomic structures on the X-ray image.

definition.value: A direct appraisal of a patient's condition by a psychiatric specialist that is based on a physical exam, medical history, and the patient's account of symptoms.
A direct appraisal of a patient's condition by a urology specialist that is based on a physical exam, medical history, and the patient's account of symptoms.
A direct appraisal of a patient's condition by an allied health professional specialist that is based on a physical exam, medical history, and the patient's account of symptoms.
The determination of the type and/or amount of vitamins in a sample.

Delivery of a gamma-emitting radioisotope (a radionuclide) into the patient, normally through injection into the bloodstream and detected by gamma camera The radioisotope could be is a simple soluble dissolved ion, such as an isotope of gallium(III), or a marker radioisotope is attached to a specific ligand to create a radioligand targeting a place of interest in the body.
Surgeical procedure to restore or replace physical defects of form or function. Physical defects could be a consequence of birth defects, trauma, or medical conditions.

value.value: Elective surgeries to improve or correct patients body imperfections or appearance. These surgeries can address imperfections due to preference, congenital, acquired, illness, or traumatic or para-physiological events such as aging.

definition.value: A procedure for increasing the size of the breast using a prosthetic implant.

value.value: A surgical procedure to remove excess skin and fat from the abdomen.

definition.value: A medically necessary surgery performed to restore function and conventional appearance of the body part. The surgery can correct deformities created by birth defects, trauma or medical conditions and is performed by a plastic surgeon.
A surgical procedure that is performed for therapeutic or cosmetic reformation of tissue.

A medically necessary surgery performed to restore function and conventional appearance of lip. The surgery can correct deformities created by birth defects, trauma or medical conditions and is performed by a plastic surgeon.

A medically necessary surgery performed to restore function and conventional appearance of secondary palate. The surgery can correct deformities created by birth defects, trauma or medical conditions and is performed by a plastic surgeon.

A medically necessary surgery performed to restore function and conventional appearance of breast. The surgery can correct deformities created by birth defects, trauma or medical conditions and is performed by a plastic surgeon.

value.value: Surgery using incisional, excisional, or use of local/regional flaps to repair burned areas.

definition.value: Surgical reconstruction or replacement of all or part of a malformed, diseased, degenerated, or otherwise damaged joint. NCIT:C51691
A surgery that fixes or mends knee joint.
A surgery that fixes or mends hip joint.
Surgical replacement of part or all of a damaged knee joint with an artificial joint.

value.value: Surgical replacement of all parts of a damaged knee joint with an artificial joint.

definition.value: The surgery to correct a torn knee ligament involves replacing the ligament with a piece of healthy tendon.

value.value: A procedure that delivers a single, highly concentrated dose of ionizing radiation from an external source to a small, precise target using 3-D computerized imaging to focus beams. There is no incision, but this technique distorts and destroys the DNA of tumor cells in a highly directed fashion.

definition.value: A type of stereotactic surgery that uses specialized equipment to focus approximately 200 beams of radiation on a tumor or other target with submillimeter accuracy.
A type of sterotactic radiosurgery using photons to treat cancerous and noncancerous abnormalities via a linear accelerator (LINAC) machine.
External radiation therapy that is directed at a specific body part/tumor over a fractionated treatment schedule.

value.value: A method of external beam radiotherapy (EBRT) that accurately delivers a high irradiation dose to an extracranial target in one or few treatment fractions

label.value: stereotactic radiosurgery using proton beam therapy

definition.value: A type of stereotactic radiosurgery that uses prroton beams.
Treatment with zinc (typically a zinc salt, like zinc acetate or zinc sulfate) with an expected therapeutic benefit.
Zinc therapy can induce metallothionein
Use of a drug that inhibits Janus kinases.

value.value: Janus kinase (JAK) Inhibitors are the latest drug class of disease-modifying medication to emerge for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis (RA). They are a small molecule-targeted treatment and are the first oral option to compare favourably to existing biologic disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs (DMARDs).

definition.value: Treatment with a substance that inhibits GABA trasaminase.
Use of a swab as the collection device to obtain clinical specimens.

value.value: Assistance provided by clinicians and public health practitioners to enhance an individual and/or their familys self-efficacy in managing one or more conditions. This assistance can include activities such as patient education, support for lifestyle modifications, and support to help individuals develop the skills needed for effective chronic disease management.

Services and supports provided to babies and young children with developmental delays and disabilities and their families. These may include speech therapy, physical therapy, and other types of services based on the needs of the child and family. They can have a significant impact on a childs ability to learn new skills and overcome challenges and can increase success in school and life.
A range of targeted services and supports that are available to babies and young children with developmental delays or specific health conditions. [ NCI ]

label.value: diabetes self health-management support and education

value.value: An education and support system that addresses the comprehensive blend of clinical, educational, psychosocial, and behavioral aspects of care needed for daily self-management and provides the foundation to help all people with diabetes navigate their daily self-care with confidence and improved outcomes.
